{
    "question_stem": "A curve has the equation \\(y = x^3 - 4x^2 + 3x\\).",
    "parts": [
        {
            "part_label": "a",
            "question_text": "Find the coordinates of the points where the curve meets the x-axis.",
            "solution_text": "The curve meets the x-axis when \\(y = 0\\).\nSo we set \\(x^3 - 4x^2 + 3x = 0\\).\nFactorising gives \\(x(x^2 - 4x + 3) = 0\\).\nFurther factorising the quadratic gives \\(x(x-1)(x-3) = 0\\).\nTherefore, \\(x = 0\\), \\(x = 1\\) and \\(x = 3\\).\nThe coordinates where the curve meets the x-axis are \\((0, 0)\\), \\((1, 0)\\) and \\((3, 0)\\)."
        }
